results.lead_paragraph: MOSCOW, Sunday, Aug. 28 (UPI)--The Soviet Union remained silent today on the fate of Luna 11. The spacecraft was launched Wednesday to orbit the moon and match the United States Lunar Orbiter 1 in a picture-taking flight to select landing sites for the first man on the moon.

headline.main: MOSCOW TRAINING FLIERS FOR HANOI; Some of North Vietnamese Called Ready for Combat in Supersonic Fighters

results.snippet: MOSCOW, Aug. 28--The Soviet Union disclosed today that it was training North Vietnamese fighter pilots at a Soviet air base to fly supersonic interceptors against United States aircraft.

byline.original: By RAYMOND H. ANDERSON Special to The New York Times
